Class WaterJug

  • java.lang.Object
    • WaterJug
  • public class WaterJug
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the driver functionality for the A Star Search as it relates to the Water Jug Problem

      • aStarSearch

        public static int aStarSearch​(int[] inBuckets,
                              int goal)
        This function calculates the aStarSearch for the given parameters of the buckets and their capacity values - OpenList keeps nodes that have not already been visited - ClosedList keeps nodes that have already been visited Each iteration contains the same principles: - Check if the current state has met the goal requirements (if so, the search is done) - Find the neighbors of the current node based on how the water can move - Add the neighbors to the list of nodes to explore if they have not already been explored or queued
        Parameters:
        inBuckets - An array that contains the capacities of each bucket
        goal - The goal amount of water that should be in the solution bucket to finish the search
        Returns:
        The number of steps taken to find the solution from the given buckets

      • nodeLocInOpenSet

        public static int nodeLocInOpenSet​(Node node,
                                   java.util.ArrayList<Node> openList)
        Search the given list of nodes yet to be visited and determine if the given node is in the open List If it is in the open list and has a smaller value f() then return the position of the found node
        Parameters:
        node - The node to search for within the given list
        openList - The list containing all nodes that are created, but have not yet been visited
        Returns:
        The location of the node or -1 if the node was not found

        public static boolean nodeInClosedSet​(Node node,

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        Whether the node was found in the list or not

      • getAllNeighbors

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Node> getAllNeighbors​(Node current)
        Finds all the possible neighbors of a give Node - Fill each bucket that is not full - Pour each bucket with water into another bucket - Empty each bucket with water in it - Pour each bucket with water in it into the solution
        Parameters:
        current - Node of the current state to find neighbors of
        Returns:
        List of all nodes that neighbor the current state node

      • solutionPossible

        public static boolean solutionPossible​(int[] inBuckets,
